  "text": "The plantaris muscle in both legs of the rats in the overloaded groups was functionally overloaded by surgical removal of its major synergists, i.e., the soleus and both heads of the gastrocnemius muscles, under anesthesia [ketamine (75 mg/kg body wt), zylazine (10 mg/kg body wt)] and aseptic conditions as described previously [CITATION_1] . In the Con S rats, the same skin incisions and connective tissue and muscle manipulations as in the FO rats were performed without removal of the plantaris synergists. Rats were allowed 4 days of recovery before treadmill training was initiated.",
