      "span_text": "The plantaris muscle in both legs of the rats in the overloaded groups was functionally overloaded by surgical removal of its major synergists, i.e., the soleus and both heads of the gastrocnemius muscles, under anesthesia [ketamine (75 mg/kg body wt), zylazine (10 mg/kg body wt)] and aseptic conditions as described previously"
